Package org.neo4j.index.internal.gbptree

Interface CleanupJob

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CleanupJob.Adaptor, GBPTreeCleanupJob
    public interface CleanupJob
    A job cleaning something up after recovery. Usually added to RecoveryCleanupWorkCollector.

    Report state of cleaning progress.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface Description
      static class  CleanupJob.Adaptor  
      static interface  CleanupJob.Executor
      Executor of asynchronous units of work needed during the recovery clean up.
      static interface  CleanupJob.JobResult<T>
      Result handle of jobs executed by CleanupJob.Executor.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field Description
      static CleanupJob CLEAN
      A CleanupJob that doesn't need cleaning, i.e. it's already clean.

    • Field Detail

      • CLEAN

        static final CleanupJob CLEAN
        A CleanupJob that doesn't need cleaning, i.e. it's already clean.

    • Method Detail

      • needed

        boolean needed()
        Returns:
        true if gbptree still needs cleaning, meaning job is not yet finished or has not started at all. false if gbptree does not need cleaning, meaning job has finished or it was never needed in the first place.

      • hasFailed

        boolean hasFailed()
        Returns:
        true if the job has failed. Use getCause() to see cause of failure.

      • getCause

        Throwable getCause()
        Returns:
        Cause of failure if hasFailed() or null if job has not failed.

      • close

        void close()
        Mark this job as closed and cleanup all it's resources.

      • run

        void run​(CleanupJob.Executor executor)
        Run cleanup job and use provided executor for parallel tasks. This method will wait for all jobs passed to executor to finish before returning.
